by Inspiratus » Wed Apr 27, 2022 9:57 pm

Monkey 569 leaped off a cliff, screaming that "IT WAKES! IT SHALL COME TO EXTEND OUR SUFFERING!"

...

"What is this? Why is the stock depleted? Have I not refilled the coffers?"

"You have, Ţ̶̧͍̳̫̥̯̭͖̘̗̝̍͋̌̾̍͌͋̀̊͑̽̉̃̚r̷̢̧̛͔̝̱͉̪̬͕̳͚̗̪̘̻̒̅̃̅̒͆̀͆̾͆͊̉́̆į̶̢̢̥̣̥͉̙̊̌̉́̂̿͜ͅp̶̟̖̺̱͚̍̀̍̉̿͝ą̸̗̝̘̹̯͉̹̮̗̙͙͈̍̎n̵͎̔͆̏š̷̙̖̬̞̈́́̋̂̏̑͒̍́͐͘̚͝i̴̢̪̥̤̭̤̤͈̗̣̻̱̓̏̂͒͂̔̎͗͗́͗͘s̶̨̲̞̐̅̽̎͗̉̏͗̊͊ů̶̬͂̾̌̌̋̾͛̊̈́̃̀̍̚͝ţ̶̫̤̥̔͌͆͂̎̄͆̈́̑̈́̚͠. Your will has been enacted upon the planet."

"Then pray tell why in my slumber there has been not been a net increase in monkeys, but a net decrease?"

"I promise, Oh Horror, that the monkeys killed have arrived. I can only assume-"

"ASSUME?ASSUME?! I, which gave you sight to see even the smallest fur on the most insignificant monkey; I, which granted you speed beyond that of light and protection that shielded the friction from space on you; I, which granted you mastery of all the scripts and guttering sounds these monkeys make to 'communicate''; I! And with these gifts you have squandered them to the point of only being able to 'assume' something?! YOU! My puppet! My creation! YOU!?"

"I- I know that the monkeys have arrived. And I know that they have been killed."

"YOU KNOW NOTHING! OR ELSE YOU WON'T BE QUIVERING AT YOUR LACK OF KNOWLEDGE! YOU HAVE PROVEN YOUSELF DRY OF KNOWLEDGE! YOU ARE REDUNDANT TO MY PURPOSES! YOU ARE NO MORE!"

"No! Please! No- A̶̧̦̗̗͍̱̖̳̭̚Ą̵̛͎̹̘̪͕̳͚̺̠̫̋͗̓̽͆̑̄̚̕͜͝͝ͅA̷̡̨̛̞͈͈͍̖̥͉͉͚̰͊͑́̆̏͋̒̿͗̉͝͝A̷͇̙̬̣̺̯͉̠̤̺̣̋̔̊͒̓͌̀̔̃̅̀̒̄͜Á̴̦͎͂̀́̌̿̄̈́́̓́̑̕͘Ą̷̱̝͔̐͂̐̓͠͝ͅA̵̜̒̅̄̍̊͐͐A̴̮̬͔̾̈́̍̽͑̔̈́̅̎̀͌̕͠͝͠H̴͉̆̀͗̿͑͛̐̕Ḩ̴̺̮̫̟̻͓̰̙͔̺̥̱̳̖̅̆͠Ḫ̸̨̺̝̯̪̣̙͗͂̇͋͒͆̀̑̾͜H̴͖͙̳̓̄̔̇͑̐̇̚͘!"

"It is time for my will to be fully enacted."

...

568 monkeys were spread on the plane that made up their ground. The plane that held the planets, the sun, the black holes, and the many galaxies whose gravitational pull warped its fabric, was ripped apart near the Earth. A horrid sound, seemingly spread from the hole itself and travelled on particles foreign to this dimension, smashed into the eardrums of so many monkeys. Many of them scream, yet are unable to hear them, and many more lay prone, bleeding from the ears and unable to process that much pain. Many others whose hearing was spared soon begged for their eyes to be taken, for they saw in the sky a most monstrous entity, with parts tangling into each other and appendages on appendages. The figure was thin and slender, but long in height, and its top was capped with a sharp tentacle that stretched and propelled itself into the surface of the earth. The friction itself caused many near the penetrating limb, but sadly not near enough to die instantly, to suffer from the influx of energy as their meat melted off the bone. What can be called a face, if only because it is the only flat surface on the twisting mass of limbs, had a gaping tear darker than blackholes and emitting all sorts of radiation that rained down upon the poor survivors. Small particles, smaller than the quarks or strings, ripped through the DNA of every monkey and caused large tumors to instantly spawn where the flesh was hit. And as the monkeys law wriggling in pain, the being spoke.

"YOU WHO STAND, I COMMEND YOU! FOR YOU HAVE PROVEN YOURSELF A HARDY BUNCH! YOU, WHO FACE DESTRUCTION! AND FOR THIS, I OFFER YOU A REWARD! I WILL RETURN THAT WHICH WAS LOST TO YOU: YOUR DEAD! YOUR DEATHS AMMUSED ME ONCE, AND IT SHALL AMUSE ME AGAIN! COME! GREET YOUR FALLED!"

From the depth of the graveyard came limbs, then head, then torso, then legs, and finally the whole body. Or, rather, what was left, for the monkeys that came were rotted husks, without intellect or instinct, without hunger or thirst. They existed solely to roam the Earth, and they were good at that. They were even better at spreading diseases, diseases that were seemingly vanquished by modern medicine but now hold resistant that can kill before the vaccine can cure. The living dead had come back.

"ENJOY WHAT I HAVE GIVEN YOU! FOR I SHALL MAKE SURE YOU GIVE THANKS!"


The being left, and in its place, 1797 monkeys were trapped in chaos.

"ASSUME?ASSUME?! "It is time for my will to be fully enacted."

568 monkeys were spread on the plane that made up their ground. The plane that held the planets, the sun, the black holes, and the many galaxies whose gravitational pull warped its fabric, was ripped apart near the Earth. A horrid sound, seemingly spread from the hole itself and travelled on particles foreign to this dimension, smashed into the eardrums of so many monkeys. Many of them scream, yet are unable to hear them, and many more lay prone, bleeding from the ears and unable to process that much pain. Many others whose hearing was spared soon begged for their eyes to be taken, for they saw in the sky a most monstrous entity, with parts tangling into each other and appendages on appendages. The figure was thin and slender, but long in height, and its top was capped with a sharp tentacle that stretched and propelled itself into the surface of the earth. The friction itself caused many near the penetrating limb, but sadly not near enough to die instantly, to suffer from the influx of energy as their meat melted off the bone. What can be called a face, if only because it is the only flat surface on the twisting mass of limbs, had a gaping tear darker than blackholes and emitting all sorts of radiation that rained down upon the poor survivors. Small particles, smaller than the quarks or strings, ripped through the DNA of every monkey and caused large tumors to instantly spawn where the flesh was hit. And as the monkeys law wriggling in pain, the being spoke.

"YOU WHO STAND, I COMMEND YOU! FOR YOU HAVE PROVEN YOURSELF A HARDY BUNCH! YOU, WHO FACE DESTRUCTION! AND FOR THIS, I OFFER YOU A REWARD! I WILL RETURN THAT WHICH WAS LOST TO YOU: YOUR DEAD! YOUR DEATHS AMMUSED ME ONCE, AND IT SHALL AMUSE ME AGAIN! COME! GREET YOUR FALLED!"

From the depth of the graveyard came limbs, then head, then torso, then legs, and finally the whole body. Or, rather, what was left, for the monkeys that came were rotted husks, without intellect or instinct, without hunger or thirst. They existed solely to roam the Earth, and they were good at that. They were even better at spreading diseases, diseases that were seemingly vanquished by modern medicine but now hold resistant that can kill before the vaccine can cure. The living dead had come back.

"ENJOY WHAT I HAVE GIVEN YOU! FOR I SHALL MAKE SURE YOU GIVE THANKS!"


The being left, and in its place, 1797 monkeys were trapped in chaos.


Monkey 547 found the bunker of Money 1590, and repairs the Oxygen line. Before being found by the Disiesed Monkeys hid inside the Bunker, slowly growing older and older over time, without running out of food, with nothing going wrong. He died old and alone.
